  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "0.Introduction"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "This document introduces the API interfaces provide by VipIncRouter and how to use them in VIP software components."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "1.Add header file in your component"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "#include \"VipIncRouter.h\""
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "2.Add dependencies in CMakeList.txt"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "# Dependencies"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "cmt_pf_module_addLibraries(Service.Nanopb)"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "cmt_pf_module_addLibraries(Service.VipIncRouter)"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "3.Define the initial and receive callback function in your component"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Next is an example function"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "void Component_Init(void)"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "{ if (E_NOT_OK == (VipIncRouter_ChnOpenClbkReg(CHANNEL_NUM, NULL, &Component_IncRxMsg))) { /*Need DLT*/ }"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "}"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "static void Component_IncRxMsg(uint8 u8ChannelNumber, uint8* au8pubuf, uint16* ps16lengthptr)"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "{"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "/*Break up and analysis the received data from au8pubuf*/"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "}"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Note:"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Component_IncRxMsg() can't call VipIncRouter_Write() synchronously. VipIncRouter_Write() MUST called asynchronously."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Otherwise OS will report OS_STATUS_NESTING_DEADLOCK due to spinlock nesting."
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/How%20to%20use%20INC%20module/image-2023-3-31_9-44-27.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/How to use INC module/image-2023-3-31_9-44-27.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "4.Define the INC frame send function in your component"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Next is an example function"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "static void Component_IncTxMsg(uint8 *pu8msg_prt, const uint8 u8MsgLength) { uint8 ch_id = Component_CHANNEL_NUMBER; int intMsgLength = 0; /*Init intMsgLength, otherwise the high byte is random*/ Std_ReturnType ret;"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "intMsgLength = (int)u8MsgLength; ret = VipIncRouter_Write(ch_id, pu8msg_prt, &intMsgLength); if(ret == E_OK) { /* Do nothing now */ } else {"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "/*Please report the ret value;  E_OK(0) E_NOT_OK(1) E_FLOWCONTROL_INACTIVE(2) E_BUFFULL(3) E_CHAN_NOPEN(4)*/"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "}"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "}"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "5.API provide by VipIncRouter"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "5.1 VipIncRouter_ChnOpenClbkReg"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "headers": [
        "Prototype",
        ""
      ],
      "rows": [
        [
          "Std_ReturnType VipIncRouter_ChnOpenClbkReg(uint8 u8ChannelNumber,FlowControlCB vipFlowCtrlCB, RecieveMsgCB vipRxMsgCB)",
          ""
        ],
        [
          "Parameter",
          ""
        ],
        [
          "u8ChannelNumber",
          "INC channel number used by your component"
        ],
        [
          "vipFlowCtrlCB",
          "Flow control callback ( If there is no flow control feature, you can use NULL )"
        ],
        [
          "vipRxMsgCB",
          "Receive message callback (It should be defined by user)"
        ],
        [
          "Return code",
          ""
        ],
        [
          "E_OK",
          "Register successfully"
        ],
        [
          "E_NOT_OK",
          "Register failed"
        ],
        [
          "Description",
          ""
        ],
        [
          "This Api will Open the channel in non blocking mode and it also registers the callback functions.",
          ""
        ]
      ]
    },
